1. This order may be cited as the Withdrawal of the United Kingdom from 
the European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act 2019 (Part 15) 
(Commencement) Order 2020.

heading: 2. The 31st day of January 2020 at 11:00 p.m. is appointed as the day on
text_raw:
2. The 31st day of January 2020 at 11:00 p.m. is appointed as the day on 
which and the time at which Part 15 of the Withdrawal of the United 
Kingdom from the European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act 2019 
(No. 8 of 2019) shall come into operation. 

GIVEN under my Official Seal, 

31 January, 2020. 

SIMON COVENEY, 

Minister for Foreign Affairs and Trade. 

Notice of the making of this Statutory Instrument was published in 
“Iris Oifigiúil” of 4th February, 2020.

EXPLANATORY NOTE 

(This note is not part of the Statutory Instrument and does not purport to be a 
legal interpretation.) 

This Order appoints the 31st day of January 2020 at 11:00 p.m. as the day and 
time on which Part 15 of the Withdrawal of the United Kingdom from the 
European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act 2019 comes into operation.
